signatureAbility.signatureDescription: Players with this ability are harder to knock out of The Zone
Players with this ability will recover from the effects of Wear and Tear and fatigue at an increased rate between plays.
Blockers with this ability will frequently attempt and win impact blocks against linebackers and defensive backs when playing as a lineman or fullback.
Blockers with this ability defend against spin pass rush moves as if they had an additional resistance point
Shutdown defenders have the talent to erase receivers from the game. When they enter the zone, their coverage is tighter and interceptions are more frequent on contested catches.
Players with this ability are more likely to succeed at and attempt diving catches and swats.
Defenders with this ability generally react much faster to receiver cut moves when in man coverage and inside the numbers
Defenders with this ability force more catch knockouts and react quicker in deep zone coverage, 20+ yards from the LoS and outside the hash marks.
Defenders with this ability generally react much faster to receiver cut moves when in man coverage
Defenders with this ability can still tackle effectively while trying to strip the football.
Some pass rushers intimidate quarterbacks with their sheer presence. When they enter the zone, they can apply significant pressure on quarterbacks even while engaged with blockers.
Defenders with this ability are less likely to increase their blocker's resistance bars when performing shed wins
Defenders with this ability have a chance to receive dominant bull rush wins when their stamina is full. This consumes additional stamina.
Defenders with this ability do not need to spend a point on shed attempts during a run play
When lined up in the slot, players with this ability have access to four additional hot routes during pre-play adjustments.
When lined up in the slot, receivers with this ability make faster cuts and have better hands when catching passes less than 10 yards from the LoS
Receivers with this ability catch more consistently while catching passes 10-20 yards from the LoS, inside the numbers
